text=!gtin2atc%0a!!Pharmacode oder GTIN Code auf ATC-Code schlüsseln.%0a* gem install gtin2atc%0a[@%0a/home/zeno/.rvm/gems/ruby-1.9.3-p551/bin/gtin2atc ver.0.1.3%0aUsage:%0a  gtin2atc [--compare] [--log] [file_with_gtin or gtin or pharmacode] [gtin..]%0a    If file_with_gtin is given only the GTIN (or pharamacode) (one per line) is outputted.%0a    If no file or gtin is given, alle GTIN will be processed.%0a    --log               log important actions%0a%0a    --compare           download an compare GTIN/ATC_code from BAG, SwissIndex and RefData%0a                        For each GTIN we will output a message if it can be only found in the%0a                        * BAG http://bag.e-mediat.net/SL2007.Web.External/File.axd?file=XMLPublications.zip%0a                        * SwissIndex e-mediat: http://swissindex.e-mediat.net/SwissindexPharma_out_V101%0a                        * or if the ATC_Code does not not match%0a    -- full             if --compare and --full given produce 15 detailed report files%0a    -h,   --help         Show this help message.%0a@]
